## What the SSP Approval Means for the Authorization Package

With the SSP approved, the Select step is complete. The authorization package at this point contains:

- System description (Task C-1) — approved
- Security categorization (Task C-2) — AO-approved
- Categorization review record (Task C-3) — signed by all reviewers
- Tailored control set with allocation and implementation documentation (Tasks S-1 through S-4)
- Continuous monitoring strategy (Task S-5)
- SSP approval memo (Task S-6)

The next step is the Implement step — where the controls documented in the SSP are actually built, configured, and deployed. For some controls, implementation is already complete (encryption was enabled, MFA was configured, audit logging was set up as part of the system deployment). For others — specifically the POA&M items — implementation is still in progress. The Implement step also includes the security configuration documentation and the initial configuration baseline capture that the assessment team will use as a reference.

